Help Type: topic
Topic: recipe

Recipes

Create an archive from Markdown:
  spinedigest create notes.sdpub ./notes.md --input-format markdown

Create an archive from EPUB:
  spinedigest create book.sdpub ./book.epub

Check readiness:
  spinedigest status book.sdpub
  spinedigest index book.sdpub

Estimate summary generation:
  spinedigest estimate book.sdpub --stage summary

Queue one chapter summary:
  spinedigest queue add book.sdpub --chapter 3 --to summary

Queue one chapter graph and watch as JSONL:
  spinedigest queue add book.sdpub --chapter 3 --to graph
  spinedigest queue watch <job-id> --jsonl

Prioritize an existing job:
  spinedigest queue boost <job-id>

Find and read source-backed knowledge:
  spinedigest find book.sdpub "knowledge graph" --type node
  spinedigest page book.sdpub --node 84

List archive objects as JSON:
  spinedigest list book.sdpub --type node --json
  spinedigest list book.sdpub --type node --chapter 3 --json
  spinedigest find book.sdpub "RAG" --type node --json

Read one chapter as continuous text:
  spinedigest read book.sdpub --chapter 3

Export a Markdown projection:
  spinedigest export book.sdpub --output-format markdown --output digest.md

Pipe Markdown into an archive:
  cat article.md | spinedigest create article.sdpub --input-format markdown

Pipe plain text into an archive:
  cat chapter.txt | spinedigest create chapter.sdpub --input-format txt

Pipe extracted webpage text into an archive:
  curl -L https://example.com/post | defuddle | spinedigest create article.sdpub --input-format markdown

Run a direct stream transform:
  cat chapter.txt | spinedigest transform --input-format txt --output-format markdown
